00:57:22.450 --> 00:57:25.390
But then one of the
hyperfine states

00:57:25.390 --> 00:57:28.740
decays because there is
some leakage, or we--

00:57:28.740 --> 00:57:31.890
I don't know-- we interrogate
this state with laser

00:57:31.890 --> 00:57:32.780
beams or such.

00:57:32.780 --> 00:57:34.380
We make it unstable.

00:57:34.380 --> 00:57:38.700
We allow this state to
decay to another state.

00:57:38.700 --> 00:57:44.120
And the question is, if we
make the decay of that level

00:57:44.120 --> 00:57:50.110
stronger and stronger, does
the decay of the initial state

00:57:50.110 --> 00:57:50.960
increase?

00:57:50.960 --> 00:57:51.510
Decrease?

00:57:51.510 --> 00:57:52.512
Or is of that?

00:57:58.010 --> 00:57:59.990
Good.

00:57:59.990 --> 00:58:03.820
So what you have learned here
