01:01:45.570 --> 01:01:50.010
So we showed in this work
that the quantum Zeno effect

01:01:50.010 --> 01:01:53.910
is the same, whether you do
a pulsed observation, which

01:01:53.910 --> 01:01:56.600
is a strong measurement, or
continuous weak measurement.

01:02:01.180 --> 01:02:01.680
OK.

01:02:01.680 --> 01:02:05.660
But let's now, after
this short interlude,

01:02:05.660 --> 01:02:07.610
go back to the master equation.

01:02:07.610 --> 01:02:19.550
So our job is now to
solve this master equation

01:02:19.550 --> 01:02:22.240
for the limit of strong damping.

01:02:22.240 --> 01:02:23.860
And what we will
find, actually, is

01:02:23.860 --> 01:02:27.180
we will find both the quantum
Zeno effect and another tidbit.

01:02:27.180 --> 01:02:29.700
We will also find
the Purcell effect,

01:02:29.700 --> 01:02:33.570
which is enhanced spontaneous
emission to a cavity.

01:02:33.570 --> 01:02:41.570
Now the way how we solve
this master equation

01:02:41.570 --> 01:02:48.450
in this limiting
case is by the method

01:02:48.450 --> 01:02:52.430
of idiopathic elimination
of coherences.

01:02:52.430 --> 01:02:56.110
And let me explain it to
you with that equation.

01:02:56.110 --> 01:03:01.120
What we have here is the
derivative of the coherences.

01:03:01.120 --> 01:03:03.240
And when you look at
the right-hand side,

01:03:03.240 --> 01:03:07.550
the derivative of the coherences
is kappa, a damping terms,

01:03:07.550 --> 01:03:09.550
times the coherence.

01:03:09.550 --> 01:03:11.820
Well, if you have
an equation which

01:03:11.820 --> 01:03:16.890
says a dot equals minus
strong damping times a,

01:03:16.890 --> 01:03:19.575
you have a very rapid
exponential damping.

01:03:22.110 --> 01:03:27.680
The system immediately
gets into an equilibrium.

01:03:27.680 --> 01:03:31.360
And the equilibrium is
given by the first term.

01:03:31.360 --> 01:03:36.990
So if you have a situation that
the population do not rapidly

01:03:36.990 --> 01:03:42.710
change, then this
equation can be

01:03:42.710 --> 01:03:47.820
written that we have
a very rapid damping.

01:03:47.820 --> 01:03:51.640
And ultimately, the
coherences settle

01:03:51.640 --> 01:03:55.070
to an quasi-equilibrium
value in a time 1

01:03:55.070 --> 01:03:59.300
over kappa, which is
given by the first term.

01:03:59.300 --> 01:04:02.010
In other words, you
set the time derivative

01:04:02.010 --> 01:04:04.110
of the left-hand side, 0.

01:04:04.110 --> 01:04:07.680
And then the coherences
are expressed

01:04:07.680 --> 01:04:10.800
in terms of the slowly
changing quantity, which

01:04:10.800 --> 01:04:14.010
are the populations.

01:04:14.010 --> 01:04:15.260
So let me repeat.

01:04:15.260 --> 01:04:19.760
If coherences are
rapidly damped,

01:04:19.760 --> 01:04:23.280
we can neglect the
time derivative

01:04:23.280 --> 01:04:25.070
of the left-hand side.

01:04:25.070 --> 01:04:28.550
And at any given
moment, the coherences

01:04:28.550 --> 01:04:32.910
will be given by an expression
which involves the population.

01:04:32.910 --> 01:04:36.700
And if the populations
slowly change,

01:04:36.700 --> 01:04:40.110
the coherences
will slowly change.

01:04:40.110 --> 01:04:43.160
Or in other words,
the coherences

01:04:43.160 --> 01:04:44.860
follow the population.

01:04:44.860 --> 01:04:48.550
And the lag time is,
at most, 1 over kappa.

01:04:48.550 --> 01:04:51.530
And we are in the
limit of strong kappa.

01:04:51.530 --> 01:04:54.950
This principle of
eliminating coherences and we

01:04:54.950 --> 01:04:57.910
simply get a master
equation for population

01:04:57.910 --> 01:05:01.700
is called the idiopathic
elimination of coherences.

01:05:01.700 --> 01:05:04.760
It's also called by Eric
Hargan in his famous work

01:05:04.760 --> 01:05:09.010
about synergy by the principle
that, if you have rapidly

01:05:09.010 --> 01:05:13.140
damped modes, they are
slaved by the slow modes.

01:05:13.140 --> 01:05:16.280
In other words, the rapidly
damped degrees of freedom

01:05:16.280 --> 01:05:18.890
follow the slow
degrees of freedom.

01:05:18.890 --> 01:05:22.090
And this is what I just said,
that the instantaneous value

01:05:22.090 --> 01:05:24.815
of the coherences is always
given by the population.

01:05:27.510 --> 01:05:30.620
So let me just write that down
and see where it takes us.

01:05:34.390 --> 01:05:41.640
So we have the
situation that we want

01:05:41.640 --> 01:05:43.940
to now look at the
case of strong damping.

01:05:46.890 --> 01:05:48.510
This is the overdamped case.

01:05:51.260 --> 01:06:05.680
And we use now the method
of idiopathic elimination

01:06:05.680 --> 01:06:13.820
of coherences, because
they are rapidly damped.

01:06:20.610 --> 01:06:22.390
And there is a
wonderful discussion

01:06:22.390 --> 01:06:27.180
about this method in
Atom-Photon interaction.

01:06:27.180 --> 01:06:35.800
It's the Exercise
18 on page 601.

01:06:35.800 --> 01:06:38.910
So mathematically,
what we assume

01:06:38.910 --> 01:06:48.030
is that the population
vary slowly.

01:06:48.030 --> 01:06:50.305
For instance, they vary
at the Rabi frequency.

01:06:54.590 --> 01:07:04.410
So therefore, we can say that
over the rapid time evolution

01:07:04.410 --> 01:07:15.160
of the coherences-- rho
1, 2 plus rho 2, 1--

01:07:15.160 --> 01:07:18.860
so this is the rapid time
evolution of the coherences.

01:07:18.860 --> 01:07:27.740
But for times which are on
the order of 1 over kappa,

01:07:27.740 --> 01:07:29.300
the population are not changing.

01:07:29.300 --> 01:07:32.660
The population change over
the much longer time scale,

01:07:32.660 --> 01:07:35.610
which is the period of
the Rabi oscillation.

01:07:35.610 --> 01:07:40.140
So therefore, for
the short time scale,

01:07:40.140 --> 01:07:44.570
I can sort of pretend that
this term is constant.

01:07:44.570 --> 01:07:50.200
And for obvious reasons, let
me now call this constant term,

01:07:50.200 --> 01:07:58.220
or slowly varying term, it is,
at least for short time scales,

01:07:58.220 --> 01:08:00.280
the equilibrium value.

01:08:00.280 --> 01:08:02.180
So the way how we
should read it is

01:08:02.180 --> 01:08:04.740
that the coherences
will very, very rapidly

01:08:04.740 --> 01:08:08.140
damp to this equilibrium value.

01:08:08.140 --> 01:08:15.240
And this equilibrium
value was given

01:08:15.240 --> 01:08:20.769
by the population,
which may slowly change.

01:08:29.020 --> 01:08:35.680
But that means, now, by
eliminating coherences,

01:08:35.680 --> 01:08:40.930
we obtain a rate equation
for the populations only.

01:08:51.640 --> 01:08:54.100
So therefore, if you
neglect short transients

01:08:54.100 --> 01:08:58.760
over the short
time 1 over kappa,

01:08:58.760 --> 01:09:01.649
the coherences are
always given by

01:09:01.649 --> 01:09:04.939
this quasi-equilibrium
value, which

01:09:04.939 --> 01:09:07.319
is expressed by the population.

01:09:07.319 --> 01:09:10.850
And therefore, we can go to
our master equation, which

01:09:10.850 --> 01:09:14.120
was a master equation
for the of diagram matrix

01:09:14.120 --> 01:09:16.990
elements of the density
matrix, and we can now

01:09:16.990 --> 01:09:20.729
replace the coherences
by an expression which

01:09:20.729 --> 01:09:22.390
involves only population.

01:09:22.390 --> 01:09:27.149
So we get now closed equations
for only the population.

01:09:27.149 --> 01:09:29.729
I'm sort of emphasizing that
because you may have asked

01:09:29.729 --> 01:09:33.219
yourself, when you have the
rate equation a la Einstein,

01:09:33.219 --> 01:09:36.009
with the a and b
coefficient, these are just

01:09:36.009 --> 01:09:38.590
rate equation for populations.

01:09:38.590 --> 01:09:41.609
But here, in our class, we've
always talked about the density

01:09:41.609 --> 01:09:44.270
matrix, how important
the coherences are.

01:09:44.270 --> 01:09:45.979
The coherences are important.

01:09:45.979 --> 01:09:50.689
Without coherences, you would
never absorb or emit light.

01:09:50.689 --> 01:09:54.340
But if the coherences can
be expressed by populations,

01:09:54.340 --> 01:09:56.340
you don't need a differential
equation for them.

01:10:01.140 --> 01:10:02.020
OK.

01:10:02.020 --> 01:10:09.090
So with that now, we
have our master equation

01:10:09.090 --> 01:10:11.680
for the population.

01:10:11.680 --> 01:10:22.230
And by just inserting
that, we find this.

01:10:22.230 --> 01:10:30.520
And we were interested
in the decay of rho 1, 1.

01:10:30.520 --> 01:10:33.400
Or this is also the population
of the atom in the excited

01:10:33.400 --> 01:10:36.110
state.

01:10:36.110 --> 01:10:39.990
If we initially start
where rho 1, 1 is large,

01:10:39.990 --> 01:10:42.260
we're interested in
the initial decay,

01:10:42.260 --> 01:10:47.560
then the population in
the ground state is small.

01:10:47.560 --> 01:10:52.090
And we find, indeed, that
there is exponential decay

01:10:52.090 --> 01:10:54.970
of the initial distribution.

01:10:54.970 --> 01:11:00.940
And the decay rate,
gamma z, gamma cavity,

01:11:00.940 --> 01:11:02.435
is given by this expression.

01:11:05.120 --> 01:11:08.796
So therefore, what we
find is-- but you know it

01:11:08.796 --> 01:11:13.910
